article.description: — Matthew Lee had 14 points as St. Peter's topped Quinnipiac 64-52 in the Metro Atlantic Conference tournament semifinals on Friday night.
article.headline: St. Peter's defeats Quinnipiac 64-52 in MAAC semifinal
article.linkText: St. Peter's defeats Quinnipiac 64-52 in MAAC semifinal
article.story: ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. -- — Matthew Lee had 14 points as St. Peter's topped Quinnipiac 64-52 in the Metro Atlantic Conference tournament semifinals on Friday night. KC Ndefo had 13 points, seven rebounds and three blocks for St. Peter's (18-11). Doug Edert added 10 points and seven rebounds. Matt Balanc had 14 points for the Bobcats (14-17). Kevin Marfo added 10 points and 11 rebounds. Dezi Jones had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
